The paper deals with the problem of incorporating new knowledge into neural networks, specifically deep convolutional neural networks, without requiring training sessions. This is a problem that falls under the category of machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with methods for incorporating new knowledge into neural networks. The second most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper specifically deals with deep convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. The third most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with neural networks and their modification. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with methods for improving the performance of neural networks. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper deals with classification tasks, which are commonly studied in natural language processing.
